ion:
  id: 08-research/july-01-2026-material-record-reframe
  title: july 01 2026 material record reframe
  type: source-summary
  status: seed-canon
  updated: 2026-07-01

source_context:
  The user reframed .yawn as a filesystem for material time, organization,
  backup, records, LLM-detected or LLM-used accesses, next-move logic, and
  GitHub access surfaces.

primary_claims:
  - .yawn should track material time, not only inner movement
  - records, backups, and access paths are part of the filesystem
  - the LLM should be able to show what it detected, read, or used
  - next moves should come with the logic that produced them
  - GitHub access and other external surfaces belong in the record layer
  - any existing test-on-base or mathematical decision logic should be located and integrated when available

implementation_decision:
  Added a records folder, material-time protocol, access logs, LLM access log,
  GitHub access log, backup log, next-move ledger, access/backup/next-move
  templates, and inspectable next-move scoring logic.

proof:
  source:
    - user-message
  claim: This file captures the user's material-record reframe and the implementation response.
  proof_state: source-summary
